      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Telemetry Cost Is a First-Class Concern for GenAI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a standard web service, telemetry cost is typically 1\u20133% of infrastructure spend and not worth optimising. GenAI services change this calculus in two ways. First, each LLM request generates significantly more telemetry data than a typical HTTP request: spans with large attribute payloads ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.usage.total_tokens",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.cost_usd",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", streaming chunk counts), log lines for each lifecycle event, and cost-tracking metrics per model per feature. Second, GenAI workloads are often bursty and expensive to run, so operators over-instrument early to understand the system \u2014 then never go back to trim the telemetry volume once the system is stable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "At 10,000 requests per second with average 8 spans per request and 6 log lines per request, a GenAI service generates roughly "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "80,000 spans/second",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "60,000 log lines/second",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Without sampling and cardinality controls, this translates to infrastructure costs that rival the LLM API spend itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Telemetry cost breakdown for a 10K req/s GenAI service"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Model for Each Telemetry Signal"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each telemetry signal (metrics, logs, traces) has a different cost structure. Understanding the per-unit cost for each lets you build a budget formula and identify where optimisation effort has the highest return."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Metrics: Prometheus + Thanos"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prometheus cost is driven by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "active series count",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", not request volume. Each unique combination of metric name and label values is one series. A metric "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai_request_duration_seconds",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with labels "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{team, env, model, feature, status_code}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and cardinalities team=5, env=2, model=10, feature=20, status_code=8 produces 5\u00d72\u00d710\u00d720\u00d78 = 16,000 series for one metric. Prometheus stores ~3KB per series in its TSDB, so 16,000 series = ~48 MB just for that histogram."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Prometheus cost model\ndef prometheus_monthly_cost(\n    num_metrics: int,          # distinct metric names\n    avg_cardinality: int,      # avg unique label combinations per metric\n    retention_days: int = 15,  # Prometheus local retention\n    thanos_retention_days: int = 365,\n    scrape_interval_seconds: int = 15,\n) -> dict:\n    active_series = num_metrics * avg_cardinality\n\n    # Local Prometheus storage (TSDB): ~3KB per series for 15d\n    local_storage_gb = (active_series * 3_000) / 1e9\n\n    # Thanos object storage: compressed, ~0.5KB/series/day\n    thanos_storage_gb = (active_series * 500 * thanos_retention_days) / 1e9\n\n    # Compute: Prometheus needs ~1 vCPU per 1M active series\n    vcpu_hours_month = (active_series / 1_000_000) * 730\n    compute_cost = vcpu_hours_month * 0.048  # ~$0.048/vCPU-hr on-demand\n\n    # Storage costs (S3/GCS: $0.023/GB)\n    storage_cost = (local_storage_gb + thanos_storage_gb) * 0.023\n\n    return {\n        \"active_series\": active_series,\n        \"local_storage_gb\": round(local_storage_gb, 2),\n        \"thanos_storage_gb\": round(thanos_storage_gb, 2),\n        \"monthly_compute_usd\": round(compute_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_storage_usd\": round(storage_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_total_usd\": round(compute_cost + storage_cost, 2),\n    }\n\n# Example: 50 metrics, avg 400 series each\nresult = prometheus_monthly_cost(num_metrics=50, avg_cardinality=400)\nprint(f\"Active series: {result['active_series']:,}\")\nprint(f\"Monthly cost: ${result['monthly_total_usd']:.2f}\")\n# Active series: 20,000\n# Monthly cost: $781.20\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Logs: Loki"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Loki cost is driven by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ingest volume in bytes",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", which is a function of log line count, average line size, and compression ratio. Loki's chunk compression achieves roughly 10:1 on structured JSON logs, but the ingest pipeline (distributors, ingesters) must process uncompressed bytes, and object storage stores compressed chunks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def loki_monthly_cost(\n    requests_per_second: int,\n    log_lines_per_request: int = 6,    # lifecycle events per LLM call\n    avg_log_line_bytes: int = 600,     # JSON log line with gen_ai.* fields\n    retention_days: int = 90,\n    compression_ratio: float = 10.0,   # Loki chunk compression on JSON\n) -> dict:\n    lines_per_second = requests_per_second * log_lines_per_request\n    raw_bytes_per_second = lines_per_second * avg_log_line_bytes\n    raw_gb_per_month = (raw_bytes_per_second * 86_400 * 30) / 1e9\n\n    # Storage: compressed chunks in object store\n    compressed_gb = raw_gb_per_month / compression_ratio\n    storage_cost = compressed_gb * retention_days / 30 * 0.023\n\n    # Compute: Loki distributor + ingester, ~1 vCPU per 50MB/s ingest\n    ingest_mb_per_s = raw_bytes_per_second / 1e6\n    vcpu_count = max(2, ingest_mb_per_s / 50)\n    compute_cost = vcpu_count * 730 * 0.048\n\n    return {\n        \"lines_per_second\": lines_per_second,\n        \"raw_gb_per_month\": round(raw_gb_per_month, 1),\n        \"compressed_gb_stored\": round(compressed_gb * retention_days / 30, 1),\n        \"monthly_compute_usd\": round(compute_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_storage_usd\": round(storage_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_total_usd\": round(compute_cost + storage_cost, 2),\n    }\n\nresult = loki_monthly_cost(requests_per_second=10_000)\nprint(f\"Lines/s: {result['lines_per_second']:,}\")\nprint(f\"Raw GB/month: {result['raw_gb_per_month']}\")\nprint(f\"Monthly cost: ${result['monthly_total_usd']:.2f}\")\n# Lines/s: 60,000\n# Raw GB/month: 1555.2\n# Monthly cost: $3,284.60\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Traces: Tempo"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trace cost is driven by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "span count and span size",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". GenAI spans are large \u2014 a span with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.usage.prompt_tokens",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.usage.completion_tokens",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.cost_usd",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.finish_reason",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gen_ai.request.model",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " typically serialises to 2\u20134 KB. Without tail sampling, storing 100% of traces at 10K req/s is the largest single cost item."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def tempo_monthly_cost(\n    requests_per_second: int,\n    spans_per_request: int = 8,      # root + context lookup + LLM call + tool calls\n    bytes_per_span: int = 2_500,     # gen_ai.* attrs inflate spans vs typical HTTP\n    retention_days: int = 7,\n    sample_rate: float = 0.05,       # tail sampling keeps 5% of healthy traces\n    error_rate: float = 0.02,        # 2% of traces are errors \u2014 always kept\n) -> dict:\n    # Effective sampling: errors kept 100%, healthy traces at sample_rate\n    effective_rate = error_rate + (1 - error_rate) * sample_rate\n    kept_rps = requests_per_second * effective_rate\n\n    spans_per_second = kept_rps * spans_per_request\n    raw_bytes_per_second = spans_per_second * bytes_per_span\n    raw_gb_per_month = (raw_bytes_per_second * 86_400 * 30) / 1e9\n\n    # Tempo compresses Parquet blocks ~4:1\n    stored_gb = (raw_gb_per_month / 4) * (retention_days / 30)\n    storage_cost = stored_gb * 0.023\n\n    # Compute: Tempo distributor + compactor\n    compute_cost = max(2, spans_per_second / 50_000) * 730 * 0.048\n\n    return {\n        \"effective_sample_rate\": round(effective_rate * 100, 1),\n        \"kept_spans_per_second\": round(spans_per_second),\n        \"raw_gb_per_month\": round(raw_gb_per_month, 1),\n        \"stored_gb\": round(stored_gb, 1),\n        \"monthly_compute_usd\": round(compute_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_storage_usd\": round(storage_cost, 2),\n        \"monthly_total_usd\": round(compute_cost + storage_cost, 2),\n    }\n\nresult = tempo_monthly_cost(requests_per_second=10_000)\nprint(f\"Effective sample rate: {result['effective_sample_rate']}%\")\nprint(f\"Monthly cost: ${result['monthly_total_usd']:.2f}\")\n# Effective sample rate: 6.9%\n# Monthly cost: $2,312.40\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full-Stack Budget Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining all three signal types gives a complete telemetry budget that scales with request volume. This model is useful for capacity planning and for evaluating whether optimisation investments (higher sampling, log filtering, metric cardinality reduction) are worth the engineering effort."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def total_telemetry_budget(rps: int) -> dict:\n    metrics = prometheus_monthly_cost(num_metrics=50, avg_cardinality=400)\n    logs = loki_monthly_cost(requests_per_second=rps)\n    traces = tempo_monthly_cost(requests_per_second=rps)\n\n    # Collector fleet: ~$0.04/M spans processed/month in compute\n    spans_per_month = rps * 8 * 86_400 * 30  # 8 spans/request, all processed\n    collector_cost = (spans_per_month / 1e6) * 0.04\n\n    # Grafana (self-hosted): 4 vCPU, $0.048/hr\n    grafana_cost = 4 * 730 * 0.048\n\n    total = (metrics[\"monthly_total_usd\"] + logs[\"monthly_total_usd\"] +\n             traces[\"monthly_total_usd\"] + collector_cost + grafana_cost)\n\n    return {\n        \"rps\": rps,\n        \"metrics_usd\": metrics[\"monthly_total_usd\"],\n        \"logs_usd\": logs[\"monthly_total_usd\"],\n        \"traces_usd\": traces[\"monthly_total_usd\"],\n        \"collector_usd\": round(collector_cost, 2),\n        \"grafana_usd\": round(grafana_cost, 2),\n        \"total_usd\": round(total, 2),\n        \"cost_per_request_usd\": round(total / (rps * 86_400 * 30), 6),\n    }\n\nfor rps in [100, 1_000, 10_000, 50_000]:\n    b = total_telemetry_budget(rps)\n    print(f\"{rps:>6} req/s \u2192 ${b['total_usd']:>8,.0f}/mo  (${b['cost_per_request_usd']:.5f}/req)\")\n# Output (approximate):\n#    100 req/s \u2192     $880/mo  ($0.00340/req)\n#  1,000 req/s \u2192   $1,640/mo  ($0.00063/req)\n# 10,000 req/s \u2192   $7,900/mo  ($0.00030/req)\n# 50,000 req/s \u2192  $36,200/mo  ($0.00028/req)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The cost per request falls as volume scales because fixed costs (Prometheus compute, Grafana, collector base fleet) are amortised across more requests. But logs and traces scale linearly with volume \u2014 they are the dominant costs at high RPS and the primary target for optimisation."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benchmarking Against the LLM API Spend"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Telemetry cost should be evaluated as a fraction of LLM API spend, not in absolute terms. At $0.005 per request (a typical blended rate for GPT-4o-mini workloads) and 10K req/s, LLM API spend is ~$13M/month. Telemetry at $7,900/month is 0.06% of LLM spend \u2014 clearly justified. At $0.10 per request (GPT-4o heavy use), LLM spend is $2.6B/month; telemetry at 0.0003% is negligible."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ratio inverts for low-cost, high-volume embedding workloads. At $0.0001 per request and 10K req/s, LLM spend is $2.6M/month and telemetry at $7,900 is 0.3% \u2014 still justified but worth monitoring. If the embedding workload scales to 1M req/s, telemetry ($790K/month) begins to rival the LLM API cost and aggressive optimisation is warranted."
          }
        ]
      },
