      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting and Enforcing a Telemetry Budget"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A telemetry budget sets a monthly spend ceiling for each signal type per team. Exceeding the budget triggers a review, not an automatic cutoff \u2014 cutting off telemetry during an incident would be worse than overspending. The budget process creates visibility and accountability without sacrificing reliability."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Per-Team Budget YAML"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# telemetry/budgets.yaml \u2014 reviewed quarterly, enforced via alerts\nbudgets:\n  - team: genai-search\n    monthly_budget_usd: 800\n    breakdown:\n      logs_usd: 450         # 90d retention, 200 req/s\n      traces_usd: 250       # 5% sample + errors, 200 req/s\n      metrics_usd: 100      # ~5,000 active series\n    alert_threshold: 0.80   # Alert at 80% of budget\n\n  - team: genai-summarisation\n    monthly_budget_usd: 1200\n    breakdown:\n      logs_usd: 700\n      traces_usd: 350\n      metrics_usd: 150\n    alert_threshold: 0.80\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Budget Burn Alert"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Prometheus alert: team approaching telemetry budget\n- alert: TelemetryBudgetBurnRate\n  expr: |\n    (\n      # Loki bytes ingested this month (approximated from distributor metric)\n      sum by (team) (\n        increase(loki_distributor_bytes_received_total[30d])\n      ) / 1e9 * 0.023   # cost per GB\n\n      +\n\n      # Tempo spans processed this month\n      sum by (team) (\n        increase(tempo_distributor_spans_received_total[30d])\n      ) / 1e6 * 0.04    # cost per M spans\n    )\n    /\n    on(team) group_left() telemetry_budget_usd   # from recording rule\n    > 0.80\n  for: 1h\n  labels:\n    severity: warning\n  annotations:\n    summary: \"Team {{ $labels.team }} has consumed > 80% of telemetry budget\"\n    description: \"Current spend: {{ $value | humanize }}% of monthly budget. Review sampling rates.\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Telemetry cost for GenAI services is dominated by logs (42%) and traces (29%), both of which scale linearly with request volume. At 10K req/s, a well-configured stack costs approximately $7,900/month \u2014 roughly 0.06\u20130.3% of LLM API spend depending on the model tier. The full cost model has three components: Prometheus active series count \u00d7 storage duration for metrics; log line count \u00d7 line size \u00d7 retention for Loki; and span count \u00d7 span size \u00d7 sample rate \u00d7 retention for Tempo. Build the budget formula before hitting production so you can detect cost regressions early: a per-team budget YAML reviewed quarterly, with an 80%-of-budget Prometheus alert, provides accountability without cutting off telemetry at the worst possible time."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
